-- 
Nine Egyptians Killed in Sectarian Clash in Cairo, MENA Reports

-- B y   M a h m o u d   K a s s e m
-- 
2011-05-08T07:43:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/nine-egyptians-killed-in-sectarian-clash-in-cairo-mena-reports.html
At least nine Egyptians were killed
and 144 injured in sectarian clashes in a working-class Cairo
district outside a church, the state-run Middle East  News Agency 
reported today, citing health officials.  Six Muslims and three Coptic Christians were killed during
the disturbances last night, the Cairo-based agency reported.
Prime Minister Essam Sharaf cancelled a trip to Bahrain and the
 United Arab Emirates  because of the violence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mahmoud Kassem at 
